Welcome to Positron, the next-generation data science IDE built for Python and R. It combines the power of a full-featured IDE with interactive data science tools for Python and R.

```{css}
/* Custom styling for the listing cards */
.listing-item-content {
    background: white;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid #3a78b1;
    transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
    position: relative;
    height: 100%;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-start;
}

/* Hover effects for the cards */
.listing-item-content:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
}

/* Styling for the title */
.listing-item-text h3 {
    margin-top: 0;
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: #2c3e50;
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
}

/* Styling for the description */
.listing-item-text p {
    margin-bottom: 15px;
    color: #5a6c7d;
    line-height: 1.6;
    flex: 1;
}

/* Ensure all cards in the same row have equal height */
.listing-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

/* Make the entire card clickable */
.listing-item-content {
    cursor: pointer;
}

/* Focus states for accessibility */
.listing-item-content:focus {
    outline: 2px solid #3a78b1;
    outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Hide ALL images in listing items */
.listing-item img,
.listing-item-image,
.listing-item-image-container,
.listing-item-thumbnail,
.listing-item-thumbnail-container {
    display: none !important;
}

/* Hide any figure elements that might contain images */
.listing-item figure,
.listing-item .figure {
    display: none !important;
}

/* Hide any elements with image-related classes */
.listing-item [class*="image"],
.listing-item [class*="thumbnail"],
.listing-item [class*="preview"] {
    display: none !important;
}
```

#### Positron might be a good fit for you if you...

-   use VS Code for data science (Python or R) but wish it included more interactive affordances for data-specific tasks like running exploratory code, examining your variables and datasets, interacting with your plots, and developing data apps such as Shiny, Streamlit, or FastAPI.
-   use JupyterLab or hosted notebook tools for data science (Python or R) and are ready for a more powerful, fully-featured IDE that still supports notebooks.
-   use RStudio and want more ability to customize or extend your IDE.
-   use additional languages beyond only Python or R in your day-to-day data science or package development work, like Rust, C++, JavaScript, or Lua.
-   want access to powerful, data-science specific AI integrations in a modern, extensible IDE.

::: {#guide-sections}
:::


::: {.callout-note}
Positron is built on [Code OSS](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode), the open-source foundation of Visual Studio Code. For general editor features like commands, settings, and source control, you can reference the [VS Code documentation](https://code.visualstudio.com/docs).
:::
